The paper proposes a new approach for multi-agent reinforcement learning, specifically for learning a centralized value function. This involves using a modified QMIX network structure and the ${Q(\lambda)}$ approach. The paper also discusses experiments on the StarCraft Multi-Agent Challenge (SMAC) benchmark. Based on this, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems). The paper also involves some aspects of robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY), which are less likely but still relevant sub-categories.
